Hi, 

Many feature phones support this option (like good old Nokias), it is very useful to dial and pass authentication to your local HMO or bank.

This feature would solve some of the IVR disconnect problems.  the existing solution with Wait and Pause (RFC wise) ,also unblock cases when ModemManager disconnect the modem if there is long menu (like it happen with PinePhone and PinePhonePro). I had witnessed that IVR that disconnect the modem may be avoided if you dial the numbers fast enough.

Is the audio only broken in one direction (which?) or in both?
Is the sound outside of calling fine? both recording and playback?
are audio profiles/ports being properly switched when in an active call?

I think answering these questions would make sense to understand the issue better
and might also point to the root of it.

Daniel wrote a good rational for OpenStack a while back: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GitCommitMessages
But that's my point: all of this belongs into the commit message.

i want to also add that there are also docs in ofono itself such as https://github.com/FuriLabs/ofono/blob/trixie/ofono/doc/supplementaryservices-api.txt

when i was working on ussd i looked at ofono docs to make it work, the xml is just for gdbo to generate bindings

But then why have hard to read code when it's super simple to fix and document where it came from? In fact I do care because I had to look at ofono code multiple times when working on interfaces and I had wished it would have been of the same style than the rest of the code/xml.

> But is that a good reason for making things hard to parse?

Not really, but then again I /usually/ don't have to look at that too closely (or much at all), so I don't want to be too nitty here.
If it's newly written code you can just amend the commit. For the rest: Sure, please do (in a separate commit up front [ideally]).
That would certainly be appreciated :)
the dump is taken from gdbus --xml, i'm assuming other ones are also taken from gdbus --xml. i'm just following conventions here.
same comment as above, perhaps a different commit fixing all styling issues of this provider?
i can do styling changes to all of ofono provider in a different commit perhaps

But is that a good reason for making things hard to parse?

From a quick check

```busctl --xml introspect```

gives better readable output. And I'd also note which ofono version was used to generate the output in the commit message and the *command* used to get it.
Ah, well. I guess nvm then :P
ofono doesn't provide them directly, so you just dump them from introspecting the bus, which would explain the formatting :-)
It has proven useful to add a reference to the repo / commit if those are picked from elsewhere. This allows other to check for changes.

Mostly nits left.

We can merge once they are addressed :rocket:
should not be split over multiple lines

btw: are these xml files coming from upstream?

If so, can we use them?

Otherwise it would still be nice if the readability could be improved by grouping tags, indenting, ...

To me It looks a bit weird looking to have 
`</method><method ...` at the beginning of the line,
but since  all other .xml in that directory are also looking the same, feel free to ignore.

For newly written code I'd like the style to be followed.

If you could change the other instance(s) as well to adhere that would be great (but I certainly won't block if you don't)

I guess it would be nice to have have a uncrustify config (and CI job) in the future.
